        <h2>Interpreting Your Digital Marksheet from Univindia Com</h2>
        <p>Your digital marksheet contains detailed information that is essential for understanding your academic standing. It is important to comprehend each section:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Subject-Wise Grading:</strong> A complete breakdown of your performance in theory, practical, and internal assessments for each individual subject.</li>
            <li><strong>Aggregate Scores:</strong> Your total marks obtained in the current examination cycle compared to the maximum marks possible for that degree level.</li>
            <li><strong>Final Result Status:</strong> This will indicate whether you have 'Passed', 'Failed', or have been awarded a 'Supplementary' (SUPP).</li>
            <li><strong>Common Technical Abbreviations:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>RW:</strong> Result Withheld (usually due to missing documents or technical discrepancies in your student record).</li>
                    <li><strong>INC:</strong> Incomplete (missing practical or internal marks).</li>
                    <li><strong>EFPT:</strong> Eligible for Final Part Third (for students moving into their final year).</li>
                    <li><strong>RL:</strong> Result Later (marks are pending but the university will update them shortly).</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>

